            <h2>Dog Care</h2>
            <br>
            <h4>How to Care for Your Dog</h4>
            <p>Proper care for your dog includes various aspects to ensure their health and happiness. Here are some essential tips:</p>
            
            <h4>Diet and Nutrition</h4>
            <p>Feed your dog high-quality food suited to their age, size, and health condition. Always ensure they have access to fresh water.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="https://www.akc.org/expert-advice/nutrition/" target="_blank">American Kennel Club: Dog Nutrition</a></li>
            </ul>
    
            <h4>Exercise and Activity</h4>
            <p>Regular exercise is crucial for your dog's physical and mental health. Aim for daily walks and playtime.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="https://www.smalldoorvet.com/learning-center/wellness/best-ways-to-exercise-with-dogs" target="_blank">The 9 Best Ways to Exercise With Your Dog</a></li>
            </ul>
    
            <h4>Grooming</h4>
            <p>Regular grooming helps keep your dog's coat clean and free of mats. Brush their fur, trim their nails, and clean their ears as needed.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="https://www.akc.org/expert-advice/grooming/" target="_blank">American Kennel Club: Dog Grooming</a></li>
            </ul>
